      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>Auburn and the surrounding regions of New York State were noted for their progressive attitudes towards penal systems.  &scrc_name; is also the repository of the papers of several prison reformers, notably <archref href="../o/osborne_fam.htm">Thomas Mott Osborne</archref>.</p><p>Several books on the murder and trial were published and are in either the Rare Books or general (circulating) collection; please refer to &summitref; and search on "Freeman, William, 1824-1847" to locate these items.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
      
